246
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:32,620
thing that sets miraculous gifts apart from the rest is really how we've been conditioned as

247
00:15:32,620 --> 00:15:35,720
perhaps Americans, perhaps even as Baptists, to look at them.

248
00:15:36,970 --> 00:15:38,770
We look at the gift of leadership, for example.

249
00:15:38,970 --> 00:15:40,330
Let me just take this as an example.

250
00:15:41,280 --> 00:15:43,480
And we see it in evidence and we think,

251
00:15:44,160 --> 00:15:47,140
now that guy, that guy is a born leader,

252
00:15:47,260 --> 00:15:48,700
or that woman is a born leader.

253
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:51,640
He's like his father, he's a chip off the old block.

254
00:15:52,220 --> 00:15:55,060
And leadership in our minds becomes something like a genetic trait,

255
00:15:55,180 --> 00:15:57,180
like saying, oh, she has her mother's eyes.

256
00:15:58,780 --> 00:16:01,820
Also, we call people born leaders no matter what kind of organization

257
00:16:02,060 --> 00:16:03,700
that they wind up working in.

258
00:16:04,410 --> 00:16:08,330
If they're the leader of a corporation or a soccer team or a platoon or a brigade

259
00:16:08,330 --> 00:16:11,890
or even an organized crime syndicate, they're still born leaders.

260
00:16:12,010 --> 00:16:15,510
Tony Soprano, to the American public, is a born leader.

261
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:19,340
Going back a generation, Michael Corleone is a born leader.

262
00:16:22,660 --> 00:16:25,620
But what I've never heard anybody say, and this is important,

263
00:16:26,470 --> 00:16:29,330
is that she has a natural talent for making cancerous tumors

264
00:16:29,330 --> 00:16:31,730
miraculously disappear when she prays.

265
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:33,820
No one says that.

266
00:16:33,820 --> 00:16:35,900
because when that sort of thing happens,

267
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:39,000
God, rightly, gets the credit.

268
00:16:41,760 --> 00:16:44,080
That is something that only he's capable of

269
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:45,420
and all of us are humble enough

270
00:16:45,420 --> 00:16:47,360
and realistic enough to admit that.

271
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:50,200
But if you think about it and just really think,

272
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:52,740
a born leader was given every tool,

273
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:55,320
every advantage of his or her upbringing,

274
00:16:56,040 --> 00:16:58,060
every ounce of wisdom, every hard knock,

275
00:16:58,180 --> 00:17:01,570
every hard lesson, every opportunity in life,

276
00:17:03,110 --> 00:17:05,230
every ounce of character strength that it takes

277
00:17:05,230 --> 00:17:13,350
to lead, not just by genetics, but by the grace of God, who is master of everything, according to the

278
00:17:13,350 --> 00:17:21,080
plans of God. In Proverbs, it says, in his heart, man plans his course, but the Lord determines his

279
00:17:21,080 --> 00:17:27,200
steps. There's nothing outside of God's control. Nothing, no character trait, no gift that develops

280
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:35,020
in a human being that isn't given and controlled and intended by God for his good purposes. And

281
00:17:35,020 --> 00:17:39,760
that's the same God who makes natural leaders who cures incurable tumors. And that's really what I

282
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:46,860
want to say as kind of a prelude to these gifts of power. Now, I also want to say that spiritual

283
00:17:46,860 --> 00:17:51,700
or supernatural gifts, quote-unquote, can be abused, just like leadership can be abused.

284
00:17:54,510 --> 00:18:01,440
Whether a leader or administrator glorifies God with his ability is his own choice. And there's

285
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:05,620
something that really might make your head spin. The same is true for people who are gifted in

286
00:18:05,620 --> 00:18:13,560
the power gifts. They can be as fraudulent and as self-serving as any leader. And Jesus pretty

287
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:18,700
much spells this out. Watch out for false prophets. They come to you in sheep's clothing, but inwardly

288
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:24,140
they are ferocious wolves. By their fruit you will recognize them. Do you think, do people pick

289
00:18:24,140 --> 00:18:29,600
grapes from thorn bushes or figs from thistles? Likewise, every good tree bears good fruit, but a

290
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:33,440
bad tree bears bad fruit. A good tree cannot bear

291
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:37,460
bad fruit, and a bad tree cannot bear good fruit. Every

292
00:18:37,460 --> 00:18:41,220
tree that does not bear good fruit is cut down and thrown into the fire.

293
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:45,780
Thus by their fruit you will recognize them. And this is the

294
00:18:45,780 --> 00:18:49,340
important part. Not everyone who says to me, Lord, Lord,

295
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:53,560
will enter the kingdom of heaven, but only he who does the will

296
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:58,200
of my Father who is in heaven. Many will say to me on that day,

297
00:18:58,200 --> 00:19:00,620
Lord, Lord, did we not prophesy in your name?

298
00:19:00,980 --> 00:19:03,760
And did we not drive out demons and perform many miracles?

299
00:19:05,260 --> 00:19:06,400
And then I will tell them plainly,

300
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:07,160
I never knew you.

301
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:08,740
Away from me, you evildoers.

302
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,660
The apostle, the great missionary Paul,

303
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:15,320
a gifted man, a church planter,

304
00:19:15,700 --> 00:19:17,620
a man who moved in miraculous signs,

305
00:19:18,260 --> 00:19:19,200
says something similar.

306
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:19,880
He says,

307
00:19:20,380 --> 00:19:22,460
And now I will show you the most excellent way.

308
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:25,520
If I speak in the tongues of men and angels

309
00:19:25,520 --> 00:19:27,540
and have not love,

310
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:30,440
I am only a resounding gong

311
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:31,620
or a clanging cymbal.

312
00:19:32,620 --> 00:19:34,140
If I have the gift of prophecy

313
00:19:34,140 --> 00:19:35,700
and I can fathom all mysteries

314
00:19:35,700 --> 00:19:36,480
and all knowledge,

315
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:37,780
and if I have faith

316
00:19:37,780 --> 00:19:38,800
that can move mountains

317
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:40,580
but have not love,

318
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:41,660
I am nothing.

319
00:19:42,480 --> 00:19:43,960
If I give all that I possess

320
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:44,520
to the poor

321
00:19:44,520 --> 00:19:45,800
and surrender my body

322
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:46,860
to the flames

323
00:19:46,860 --> 00:19:48,340
but have not love,

324
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:50,020
I gain nothing.

325
00:19:52,420 --> 00:19:53,180
It doesn't matter

326
00:19:53,180 --> 00:19:55,160
how dazzling or remarkable

327
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:56,500
your gifts are to other people.

328
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:57,800
It doesn't matter to God

329
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:58,580
in any case.

330
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:00,960
God cares first and foremost

331
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:01,720
about the heart

332
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:03,060
of the gifted person.

333
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:09,700
So as we go through and define the differences between so-called power gifts and maybe the rest,

334
00:20:10,320 --> 00:20:14,760
understand that these gifts are meant to glorify God, not a single individual.

335
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:20,560
They're meant to lift up his church, not lift up the reputation of a single man or woman.

336
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:27,840
And if they're used for any other reason, it doesn't matter how impressive or dazzling or miraculous they may appear to be.

337
00:20:28,380 --> 00:20:32,400
They cause harm, and they cause hurt, and they cause division and misunderstanding,

338
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:36,640
and that, ladies and gentlemen, is what I really want to avoid this morning

339
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:37,840
as I go through some of these.

340
00:20:39,580 --> 00:20:42,120
Now, as I go through each one, we're going to start with a gift of deliverance.

341
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:44,720
I've given several scripture verses.

342
00:20:45,020 --> 00:20:47,400
You can jot these down. I'm not going to read these.

343
00:20:47,540 --> 00:20:50,120
I'm not even going to read their addresses.

344
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:54,620
But these are for you to do further investigation if you're so inclined.

345
00:20:54,740 --> 00:20:56,980
And it's not an exhaustive list.

346
00:20:57,720 --> 00:21:00,020
There's a lot more to be said about each of these gifts.

347
00:21:00,020 --> 00:21:02,760
These are just some helps that I've provided for you this morning.

348
00:21:04,140 --> 00:21:06,240
Okay, starting with the gift of deliverance.

349
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:12,600
Anyone familiar with the life of Jesus knows that he and his disciples drove out demons.

350
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:17,060
They confronted and expelled evil spirits from people,

351
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:20,840
and they confronted and expelled evil spirits from sometimes places.

352
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:27,220
And in the modern church, though, resistance to what we think of as superstition

353
00:21:28,560 --> 00:21:33,560
or our fear that's born out of historic tragedies like the Salem witch trials

354
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:36,660
or, you know, going back a little farther, the Spanish Inquisition,

355
00:21:37,060 --> 00:21:43,180
makes us kind of, well, cynical about people being punished or marginalized

356
00:21:43,180 --> 00:21:48,260
for being demonically possessed or having demonic influence in their life.

357
00:21:49,030 --> 00:21:53,360
But most of all, more than any cynicism about demons,

358
00:21:53,480 --> 00:22:00,000
we rely on scientifically verifiable facts, about empirically provable things.

359
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:03,620
That's how we gauge truth in modern America.

360
00:22:03,620 --> 00:22:09,280
And that makes a lot of us skeptical about things like demons

361
00:22:09,280 --> 00:22:12,140
that we can't necessarily quantify or touch, taste, or see.

362
00:22:14,460 --> 00:22:18,040
I say this to our shame.

363
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:22,500
Because unfortunately, while we Americans and we American Christians

364
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:25,610
have become skeptical about this stuff,

365
00:22:25,830 --> 00:22:30,050
the rest of the world and more and more of the culture in this country,

366
00:22:31,070 --> 00:22:32,830
around us, around this place,

367
00:22:33,740 --> 00:22:37,260
have gotten reacquainted with spiritualism and supernatural power,

368
00:22:37,740 --> 00:22:40,800
though not necessarily God's supernatural power.

369
00:22:42,180 --> 00:22:43,780
So the so-called New Age movement,

370
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:44,940
many of you have heard of that,

371
00:22:44,980 --> 00:22:47,660
the popularity and rise of Eastern religions here,

372
00:22:47,740 --> 00:22:49,100
like Hinduism and Buddhism,

373
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:52,220
the re-emergence of different pagan faiths

374
00:22:52,220 --> 00:22:54,760
in a loose kind of way,

375
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:57,280
witchcraft, belief in horoscopes,

376
00:22:57,760 --> 00:23:00,500
all these are signs of a spiritually hungry culture.

377
00:23:02,550 --> 00:23:05,350
And they're signs that we have people in this culture

378
00:23:05,350 --> 00:23:07,350
that will dabble in just about anything

379
00:23:07,350 --> 00:23:09,170
to connect with a spiritual force

380
00:23:09,170 --> 00:23:12,150
that is maybe somehow bigger than them and their little lives.

381
00:23:14,690 --> 00:23:17,330
And I'm not going to go through and try and challenge or debunk

382
00:23:17,330 --> 00:23:20,050
any of these different spiritual practices.

383
00:23:20,650 --> 00:23:26,290
In fact, I believe that many of these do conjure up real spiritual power.

384
00:23:26,910 --> 00:23:29,050
And I believe that some of it is even miraculous.

385
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:32,560
But I hold to this statement absolutely.

386
00:23:34,510 --> 00:23:37,190
Any spiritual power that isn't from God's Spirit,

387
00:23:37,850 --> 00:23:41,530
that doesn't hold Christ as its only power and authority,

388
00:23:41,530 --> 00:23:44,110
is evil and

389
00:23:44,110 --> 00:23:48,070
inherently dangerous. Think of it

390
00:23:48,070 --> 00:23:50,170
like chemotherapy. It may destroy

391
00:23:50,170 --> 00:23:52,130
cancer. And I say this with all

392
00:23:52,130 --> 00:23:54,090
due respect to those of you who have gone through this.

393
00:23:55,160 --> 00:23:56,060
But sometimes

394
00:23:56,060 --> 00:23:58,660
the cure is just as bad

395
00:23:58,660 --> 00:24:00,640
as the disease. Chemotherapy

396
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:02,740
can cause hair loss and nausea

397
00:24:02,740 --> 00:24:04,800
and in rare cases it can even

398
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:06,660
kill healthy cells

399
00:24:06,660 --> 00:24:11,250
that kill the body. The gift

400
00:24:11,250 --> 00:24:13,130
of deliverance is the power of God

401
00:24:13,130 --> 00:24:15,190
given by God to weaken

402
00:24:15,190 --> 00:24:20,210
and ultimately destroy the hold evil spirits have on people and places.

403
00:24:21,580 --> 00:24:26,040
I challenge you to re-read some of the passages I've had listed above.

404
00:24:26,420 --> 00:24:27,520
Re-read the life of Christ.

405
00:24:27,740 --> 00:24:31,340
He considered these things as real as science.

406
00:24:33,310 --> 00:24:35,650
And I myself have some experience with this,

407
00:24:36,010 --> 00:24:39,870
but I think of myself in all humility as a novice in this area.

408
00:24:40,710 --> 00:24:44,210
There are places in this world, particularly on the foreign mission field,

409
00:24:44,210 --> 00:24:47,380
where evil spirits are worshipped.

410
00:24:47,380 --> 00:24:49,440
and they just show up a lot more

411
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:51,760
and they make this kind of ministry much more common

412
00:24:51,760 --> 00:24:56,300
than it has been historically here in scientific America.

413
00:24:58,950 --> 00:25:00,170
And also I want to say this.

414
00:25:00,210 --> 00:25:03,310
This is a quick plug for a class we're going to be offering in the near future.

415
00:25:03,430 --> 00:25:05,090
October 13th, I believe, it starts.

416
00:25:05,610 --> 00:25:08,810
John Ingram, a professor of psychology at Rosemead and Biola,

417
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:13,620
will be beginning a class here on spiritual warfare and deliverance

418
00:25:13,620 --> 00:25:16,680
that will answer questions that I haven't even raised this morning.

419
00:25:17,290 --> 00:25:19,390
I strongly recommend you take this class

420
00:25:19,390 --> 00:25:22,430
whether or not you feel you have the gift of deliverance or not,

421
00:25:22,790 --> 00:25:27,060
simply because our culture is dabbling in this stuff,

422
00:25:27,680 --> 00:25:30,120
ignorantly, with some horribly dangerous stuff.

423
00:25:30,660 --> 00:25:33,260
And the issue of deliverance is only going to become more real

424
00:25:33,260 --> 00:25:35,660
and a lot larger than it already is now.

425
00:25:37,650 --> 00:25:39,610
Moving on, the gift of discernment.

426
00:25:42,570 --> 00:25:44,770
Discernment and deliverance usually go hand in hand.

427
00:25:45,250 --> 00:25:47,710
Discernment is the ability God gives Christians

428
00:25:47,710 --> 00:25:50,590
to tell the difference between truth and deception.

429
00:25:52,660 --> 00:25:53,900
This is in truth and deception

430
00:25:53,900 --> 00:25:56,740
in things that are preached, taught, or spoken.

431
00:25:56,880 --> 00:26:00,160
This gift can provide those who have it

432
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:02,080
with insight into the deepest source

433
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,280
of a certain teaching,

434
00:26:03,700 --> 00:26:05,630
whether it's true or false,

435
00:26:06,500 --> 00:26:08,420
whether it comes from God,

436
00:26:09,100 --> 00:26:11,100
whether it comes from human wisdom alone,

437
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:13,500
or whether it comes from Satan himself.

438
00:26:14,450 --> 00:26:15,930
That's the gift of discernment.

439
00:26:16,450 --> 00:26:19,350
They can see this in what is said

440
00:26:19,350 --> 00:26:27,550
and what is believed. And closely related to that is the gift of faith. Every Christian is called

441
00:26:27,550 --> 00:26:35,860
to trust the Lord in good times and in bad. That's just discipleship 101. Some of us, however, seem

442
00:26:35,860 --> 00:26:42,340
to have a special gift of really resilient faith. You might call it the kind of faith that can move

443
00:26:42,340 --> 00:26:47,860
mountains. That's the sort of faith I'm talking about. And these are the sort of people that kind

444
00:26:47,860 --> 00:26:52,940
of scare and puzzle the rest of us. I mean, let's be honest. Because they don't shy away from any

445
00:26:52,940 --> 00:27:00,030
uncertainties are risks. When they're sure that something, that some end, that some goal is the

446
00:27:00,030 --> 00:27:07,130
will of God, they pursue it with no apologies. And we call these people visionaries, or depending on

447
00:27:07,130 --> 00:27:13,040
our point of view, we call them nuts. But in any case, these are the sorts of people who will look

448
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:18,680
and build toward the future with a great deal of certainty and without flinching. They have

449
00:27:18,680 --> 00:27:25,700
unusual confidence. Also, I want to talk a little bit more about this gift of faith. I'm not going

450
00:27:25,700 --> 00:27:29,960
to go into the dangers, kind of the flip side of every gift, as we

451
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:33,720
kind of define them this morning. But I do want to say that this

452
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:37,880
gift of faith has three pitfalls, and they're to be

453
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:42,010
watched out for, especially if you have this gift. The first one

454
00:27:42,010 --> 00:27:45,840
is that these people, much like

455
00:27:45,840 --> 00:27:49,220
our skit today, tend to project their gifts onto others.

456
00:27:50,090 --> 00:27:54,370
They say things like, why can't everyone be as full of faith or believe God or trust

457
00:27:54,370 --> 00:27:58,930
God like I do. And they'll often rush to judgment about

458
00:27:58,930 --> 00:28:02,110
the small-mindedness, weak faith, kind of

459
00:28:02,110 --> 00:28:09,510
spiritual weakness of those around them, while these other believers

460
00:28:09,510 --> 00:28:12,990
who may not be similarly gifted are just trying to be realistic.

461
00:28:13,530 --> 00:28:17,790
They're just trying to be responsible and realistic. So if you have this gift,

462
00:28:19,120 --> 00:28:21,960
avoid projecting your gift onto other people. Also,

463
00:28:22,980 --> 00:28:25,940
it tends to be hard for people with this gift to admit that,

464
00:28:25,940 --> 00:28:29,680
hey, sometimes, no matter how much faith they have, they can be wrong.

465
00:28:31,250 --> 00:28:34,530
See, getting them to admit they are wrong is painful,

466
00:28:34,890 --> 00:28:37,950
especially when the vision that they have goes unfulfilled.

467
00:28:38,630 --> 00:28:42,790
And the reason is simple. Sometimes those with this gift will take personal criticism,

468
00:28:43,370 --> 00:28:46,830
criticism of their vision, as criticism of God. It's simple.

469
00:28:47,210 --> 00:28:50,690
The vision is being questioned. They believe their vision is from God.

470
00:28:51,450 --> 00:28:55,410
And so they feel that God is ultimately being questioned.

471
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:02,340
The most important thing for those gifted with faith

472
00:29:02,340 --> 00:29:04,060
is just to remember humility,

473
00:29:05,300 --> 00:29:06,520
patience above all else,

474
00:29:06,900 --> 00:29:08,860
and finally, just how to roll with criticism.

475
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:12,140
How to realize that everybody may not be

476
00:29:12,140 --> 00:29:14,260
up to your standards.

477
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:17,960
That's all I'm going to say about that this morning.

478
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:19,880
But that projection issue, by the way,

479
00:29:20,200 --> 00:29:22,860
applies to almost every gift I discuss this morning.

480
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:23,740
If you have it,

481
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:26,040
and the people around you may not have it,

482
00:29:26,840 --> 00:29:28,160
don't expect them to have it.

483
00:29:29,020 --> 00:29:33,480
God has purposed a very distinct and very special thing for their lives,

484
00:29:33,540 --> 00:29:35,040
and it may not be what's up your alley.

485
00:29:35,730 --> 00:29:36,730
The gift of healing.

486
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:40,520
The gift of healing is, again, a lot like faith.

487
00:29:40,660 --> 00:29:44,600
All of us who follow Christ are called to pray for those who are sick.

488
00:29:45,800 --> 00:29:48,120
This is one of the most common requests, for example,

489
00:29:48,180 --> 00:29:50,060
that we receive as a staff when we meet.

490
00:29:51,170 --> 00:29:54,990
Various prayers for either themselves or their loved ones,

491
00:29:55,070 --> 00:29:56,770
just to recover from an illness or an injury.

492
00:29:57,610 --> 00:30:00,850
But again, there are men and women who pray for the sick

493
00:30:00,850 --> 00:30:02,690
and get results more often than most.

494
00:30:04,130 --> 00:30:05,490
And understanding here is the key.

495
00:30:05,990 --> 00:30:07,890
God heals the sick.

496
00:30:08,370 --> 00:30:11,010
Those who pray can only claim that they have a special sensitivity

497
00:30:11,010 --> 00:30:15,510
to God's desire to heal the sick in certain instances,

498
00:30:16,070 --> 00:30:17,010
not all instances.

499
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:21,220
Sometimes people gifted with healing will also realize early on

500
00:30:21,220 --> 00:30:25,400
before anyone else that God may have some other kind of purpose

501
00:30:25,400 --> 00:30:27,480
in this illness or injury.

502
00:30:27,960 --> 00:30:31,120
And at that point, what they can do in their prayers is offer comfort,

503
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:35,660
and they can even continue to offer prayers for healing and deliverance from this illness.

504
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:40,380
But in the end, they have to recognize that this is God's power,

505
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,140
and therefore God's decision.

506
00:30:44,910 --> 00:30:49,110
People gifted in healing should never blame someone else's lack of faith

507
00:30:49,110 --> 00:30:52,250
for they or their loved one's continued illness.

508
00:30:53,330 --> 00:30:56,150
That's abusive, and I can't emphasize that enough.

509
00:30:56,650 --> 00:30:59,810
And also, a person gifted with healing must always acknowledge

510
00:30:59,810 --> 00:31:01,190
that God uses medicine,

511
00:31:01,730 --> 00:31:02,950
that God uses technology

512
00:31:02,950 --> 00:31:05,010
and doctors and midwives and healers,

513
00:31:05,230 --> 00:31:06,920
as well as prayer,

514
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:10,040
and that one is never a substitute for the other.

515
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:15,320
Now this one is a bit sticky,

516
00:31:18,050 --> 00:31:19,170
or these two, I should say,

517
00:31:19,210 --> 00:31:19,770
is a bit sticky,

518
00:31:20,130 --> 00:31:22,030
because we don't commonly practice it

519
00:31:22,030 --> 00:31:25,350
in our circles.

520
00:31:28,420 --> 00:31:29,820
First off, I would like to say

521
00:31:29,820 --> 00:31:32,780
that I myself and the pastoral leadership

522
00:31:32,780 --> 00:31:36,060
of this church affirm the gift of tongues.

523
00:31:37,240 --> 00:31:40,860
We believe that they have continued validity in this day and age like any other,

524
00:31:41,120 --> 00:31:43,920
as they did in the lifetime of the apostles.

525
00:31:47,520 --> 00:31:52,280
We believe that these gifts are currently in action around the world,

526
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:56,500
including our own country, including people that we call brothers and sisters.

527
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:04,100
And I think it would be wrong if we discouraged or forbid them, even here,

528
00:32:04,600 --> 00:32:06,060
even though we're not familiar with them.

529
00:32:06,680 --> 00:32:09,500
I also acknowledge that there's a lot of confusion about speaking in tongues.

530
00:32:09,500 --> 00:32:15,580
and its place and its place in the kind of the overall life of the church so let's see if i can

531
00:32:15,580 --> 00:32:25,830
clarify that this morning some swear by it some would just as soon do without it simply put the

532
00:32:25,830 --> 00:32:30,650
gift of tongues enable a believer to use a god-given language that they have never learned

533
00:32:30,650 --> 00:32:35,630
this gift can be used in personal prayer time for the edification of the individual

534
00:32:35,630 --> 00:32:41,150
or in public for the benefit of those listening when it is used in public it must

535
00:32:42,410 --> 00:32:45,210
Underline must be followed by an interpretation.

536
00:32:45,570 --> 00:32:49,290
That is, someone translating the prayer offered in tongues

537
00:32:49,290 --> 00:32:51,810
into a language that everybody present can understand.

538
00:32:53,370 --> 00:32:55,650
Now that's the technical definition of tongues.

539
00:32:56,050 --> 00:32:58,250
Here's a few personal words about tongues.

540
00:32:58,450 --> 00:32:59,150
I pray in tongues.

541
00:33:00,290 --> 00:33:01,630
I feel like I'm coming out.

542
00:33:02,030 --> 00:33:03,230
I pray in tongues.

543
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:05,460
I've always prayed in tongues.

544
00:33:05,780 --> 00:33:07,320
I've always felt like praying in tongues.

545
00:33:09,080 --> 00:33:10,980
Actually, I became acquainted with tongues

546
00:33:10,980 --> 00:33:14,340
through my involvement with an Assemblies of God church

547
00:33:14,340 --> 00:33:15,340
while I was in college.

548
00:33:17,240 --> 00:33:18,680
I continue to pray in tongues.

549
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:20,360
I don't do it as often as I used to,

550
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:22,680
probably just because I'm not surrounded by others

551
00:33:22,680 --> 00:33:24,860
who do it with great frequency.

552
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:28,160
And I always do it in privacy.

553
00:33:29,300 --> 00:33:30,840
That's just a choice that I've made.

554
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,660
I also came from a faith tradition,

555
00:33:33,820 --> 00:33:36,600
this Assemblies of God tradition that I alluded to,

556
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:40,300
that I think puts way too much emphasis on this gift,

557
00:33:40,440 --> 00:33:41,920
especially over and above others.

558
00:33:44,890 --> 00:33:46,710
they tend to treat those without it

559
00:33:46,710 --> 00:33:48,570
as if they were somehow second-class believers.

560
00:33:49,350 --> 00:33:54,550
And treating tongues like that is just wrong-headed.

561
00:33:54,710 --> 00:33:57,130
It's not an Eagle Scout merit badge

562
00:33:57,130 --> 00:33:58,650
for the Christian to wear.

563
00:34:00,230 --> 00:34:02,490
It's a gift, like any other,

564
00:34:03,890 --> 00:34:05,610
not more powerful than any other,

565
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:08,440
used for God's purposes like any other.

566
00:34:09,040 --> 00:34:12,280
And if it's used to cause division

567
00:34:12,280 --> 00:34:14,180
or inspire fear

568
00:34:14,180 --> 00:34:17,200
or create a sense of holier-than-thou

569
00:34:17,200 --> 00:34:20,140
or I'm a better believer, I'm closer to God,

570
00:34:20,200 --> 00:34:21,820
then it's being used in a wrong way.

571
00:34:22,720 --> 00:34:24,740
Paul says this, among other things, about tongues.

572
00:34:24,740 --> 00:34:27,040
And this should give us some perspective.

573
00:34:27,680 --> 00:34:30,440
If you give a blessing using your private prayer language,

574
00:34:30,860 --> 00:34:33,590
Paul's kind of paraphrase of tongues,

575
00:34:34,530 --> 00:34:35,670
which no one else understands,

576
00:34:35,990 --> 00:34:38,030
how can some outsider who has just shown up

577
00:34:38,030 --> 00:34:40,050
and has no idea what's going on,

578
00:34:40,130 --> 00:34:42,250
know what to say, know when to say amen?

579
00:34:43,980 --> 00:34:45,380
Your blessing might be beautiful,

580
00:34:46,430 --> 00:34:48,570
but you have effectively cut that person out of it.

581
00:34:48,930 --> 00:34:54,130
I'm grateful for God for the gift of praying in tongues that he gives us for praising him,

582
00:34:54,130 --> 00:34:57,310
which leads to wonderful intimacies we enjoy with him.

583
00:34:58,290 --> 00:35:03,510
I entered into this as much as any of you, but when I'm in a church assembled for worship,

584
00:35:04,370 --> 00:35:08,250
I'd rather say five words that everyone can understand and learn from

585
00:35:08,250 --> 00:35:10,910
than say 10,000 words that sound like gibberish.

586
00:35:13,080 --> 00:35:19,760
In other words, church, our first priority in worship is communicating the truth of God.

587
00:35:22,070 --> 00:35:24,670
not dazzling people with an unintelligible language

588
00:35:24,670 --> 00:35:29,130
or weirding them out with our kind of crazy Holy Roller antics,

589
00:35:29,370 --> 00:35:30,770
doing something just because we can.

590
00:35:31,960 --> 00:35:34,740
People with this gift should always keep Paul's words in mind.

591
00:35:37,350 --> 00:35:38,190
The gift of miracles.

592
00:35:38,330 --> 00:35:42,550
And I realize this is a quick kind of Disneyland tour of these gifts.

593
00:35:42,710 --> 00:35:45,470
I think each of these deserves a sermon in its own right,

594
00:35:45,630 --> 00:35:48,730
but I want to get them in your mind and on your radar screen.

595
00:35:49,750 --> 00:35:50,690
The gift of miracles.

596
00:35:51,270 --> 00:35:54,620
The gift of miracles is closely related to the gifts of healing

597
00:35:54,620 --> 00:35:59,190
and faith. Those gifted are the human instruments that God

598
00:35:59,190 --> 00:36:02,930
uses to perform powerful acts that pretty much surpass

599
00:36:02,930 --> 00:36:06,970
and blow away any natural laws. This gift is pretty

600
00:36:06,970 --> 00:36:11,110
self-explanatory, but I should add this. God is

601
00:36:11,110 --> 00:36:15,340
no magician. He doesn't do miracles just to ooh and ah and impress

602
00:36:15,340 --> 00:36:19,400
the crowd. A miracle of God communicates something of vital

603
00:36:19,400 --> 00:36:23,810
importance. It's not a freak show. Some

604
00:36:23,810 --> 00:36:28,570
specific message to the people who witness and hear about the miracle must be communicated through

605
00:36:28,570 --> 00:36:37,050
the miracle. For example, one that most of you know, the Red Sea. The Red Sea was not done just

606
00:36:37,050 --> 00:36:43,470
to amaze the Israelites. It was done to save them from an army that was coming crashing down on them

607
00:36:43,470 --> 00:36:49,290
and was going to wipe them out because they had nowhere to go. That miracle was done for a specific

608
00:36:49,290 --> 00:36:56,170
purpose, in a specific time, in a specific place. And ultimately, it was done to glorify God,

609
00:36:57,710 --> 00:37:06,590
his power that could save when nothing else could. The gift of prayer. Prayer is something that all

610
00:37:06,590 --> 00:37:13,780
of us share in common, again, like faith. It's every Christian's privilege and joy to speak

611
00:37:13,780 --> 00:37:20,710
directly to God. You don't need to be mediated through me, or a priest, or an angel, or a rosary

612
00:37:20,710 --> 00:37:26,750
bead or anything. It is your privilege. It is your right as someone who calls Christ Lord to talk

613
00:37:26,750 --> 00:37:35,210
to God in Christ. The gift of prayer is seen, though, in the lives of believers who can pray

614
00:37:35,210 --> 00:37:42,880
over long periods of time and faithfully see tangible results coming from their prayers.

615
00:37:45,180 --> 00:37:49,460
And these kind of folks are particularly determined prayer warriors, if you know any of them or if you

616
00:37:49,460 --> 00:37:55,580
are one yourself, they seem capable of praying intensely and intently for pretty much hours on

617
00:37:55,580 --> 00:38:01,260
end. And the real kicker is that they love every minute of it. And I have to tell you, in all

618
00:38:01,260 --> 00:38:08,850
honesty, I do love prayer, but I'm not that gifted. I've known people who have, and their

619
00:38:08,850 --> 00:38:17,700
prayer life dwarfs my own. And I respect them because of it. The gift of prophecy.

620
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:23,600
Prophecy doesn't necessarily make vague, scary, apocalyptic predictions

621
00:38:23,600 --> 00:38:25,180
like Nostradamus or something.

622
00:38:26,210 --> 00:38:29,930
You know, wearing a cow and getting a wide-eyed crazy look in your eyes.

623
00:38:30,530 --> 00:38:33,590
In fact, if you can try and push that image out of your mind

624
00:38:33,590 --> 00:38:37,300
when we consider this gift, you'd be doing yourself a favor.

625
00:38:37,420 --> 00:38:41,360
Because more often than not, prophecy means speaking with God's authority

626
00:38:41,360 --> 00:38:45,080
on a concrete situation that is happening not so much in the future

627
00:38:45,080 --> 00:38:46,500
but in the here and now.

628
00:38:48,190 --> 00:38:51,250
Prophecy also doesn't have to mean the message is doom and gloom.

629
00:38:52,270 --> 00:38:54,910
Prediction of apocalyptic destruction, for example.

630
00:38:55,660 --> 00:39:00,100
A prophet can just as easily offer God's encouragement through a tough situation.

631
00:39:01,890 --> 00:39:03,590
The most basic definition is this.

632
00:39:03,590 --> 00:39:08,450
The Christian receives a message from God and communicates it with other people.

633
00:39:09,260 --> 00:39:09,920
That's a prophet.

634
00:39:12,160 --> 00:39:17,500
Again, I think exercising this gift with caution is, like all these gifts, just wise.

635
00:39:17,500 --> 00:39:19,860
if you're recently

636
00:39:19,860 --> 00:39:21,720
discovering that God

637
00:39:21,720 --> 00:39:22,860
uses you in this way

638
00:39:22,860 --> 00:39:26,120
take your message to a few mature Christians

639
00:39:26,120 --> 00:39:28,020
before you broadcast it on the internet

640
00:39:28,020 --> 00:39:29,520
or in front of this congregation

641
00:39:29,520 --> 00:39:32,560
especially those with discernment

642
00:39:32,560 --> 00:39:34,260
gifts, take your message to those

643
00:39:34,260 --> 00:39:35,640
who have the gift of discernment

644
00:39:35,640 --> 00:39:38,040
so they can double check whether this message

645
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:39,400
should even be given to others

646
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:42,270
or who if anybody should receive this message

647
00:39:42,270 --> 00:39:44,470
be gentle

648
00:39:44,470 --> 00:39:46,910
be wise and be loving no matter

649
00:39:46,910 --> 00:39:47,910
what the message is

650
00:39:47,910 --> 00:39:52,340
and rely on otherwise mature people's discretion.

651
00:39:57,580 --> 00:40:00,460
And finally, the last gift, which,

652
00:40:04,460 --> 00:40:06,020
well, if some of you identify with this,

653
00:40:06,200 --> 00:40:07,860
I'd really like to talk to you, actually,

654
00:40:07,960 --> 00:40:11,280
because I'll have an insight into a person I've never met before.

655
00:40:13,600 --> 00:40:15,240
In fact, if we had a table out front

656
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:17,520
enlisting people with the experience,

657
00:40:18,100 --> 00:40:19,520
with the gift of suffering,

658
00:40:20,670 --> 00:40:23,530
to come experience suffering for the kingdom of God,

659
00:40:23,690 --> 00:40:25,250
I wonder how long the line would be.

660
00:40:25,330 --> 00:40:26,190
I mean, let's be honest.

661
00:40:26,190 --> 00:40:31,290
and yet we know through stories of men and women who have served

662
00:40:31,290 --> 00:40:35,090
particularly in oppressive parts of the world, in Muslim or

663
00:40:35,090 --> 00:40:40,520
communist parts of the world, that unjust suffering and sometimes even

664
00:40:40,520 --> 00:40:44,620
martyrdom happens to the most thoroughly undeserving

665
00:40:44,620 --> 00:40:50,480
people, undeserving saints. The gift of suffering

666
00:40:50,480 --> 00:40:54,440
if you want to call it a gift, is not the opportunity

667
00:40:54,440 --> 00:41:00,060
to suffer. In one way or another all of us has to deal with suffering

668
00:41:00,060 --> 00:41:05,420
but the gift involves God giving particular people

669
00:41:05,420 --> 00:41:08,980
the strength and the high spirits to treat their sufferings

