00:41:08,980 --> 00:41:14,270
as if they were somehow a victory. These people can maintain an attitude of

671
00:41:14,270 --> 00:41:16,690
victory in the most apparently hopeless situations

672
00:41:16,690 --> 00:41:21,820
and all anyone can really ultimately say about this gift

673
00:41:21,820 --> 00:41:27,360
is this, if the prospect frightens you then you may not have the gift of

674
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:31,520
suffering but as is the case with so many things

675
00:41:32,560 --> 00:41:35,300
We never know for sure until we find ourselves in a situation

676
00:41:35,300 --> 00:41:40,120
what we can actually endure or what we could actually cope with.

677
00:41:42,500 --> 00:41:47,340
I also know that God, in His mercy, never tests us beyond our endurance.

678
00:41:59,780 --> 00:42:02,820
I hope I've created understanding and not more questions

679
00:42:02,820 --> 00:42:04,860
in going through all of these.

680
00:42:05,700 --> 00:42:09,540
I hope that a lot of you, or even some of you,

681
00:42:09,540 --> 00:42:13,960
have had those aha moments that I alluded to at the beginning of the sermon,

682
00:42:14,280 --> 00:42:16,500
that you see yourself in these descriptions.

683
00:42:16,600 --> 00:42:23,400
that's wonderful. But in the end, let me just reemphasize that blessing and vitality come

684
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:30,440
when a church is willing to see its people operate in these powerful ways. But we should

685
00:42:30,440 --> 00:42:36,760
also keep this in mind. God does spectacular things through flawed and thoroughly unspectacular

